  "text": "Terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase dUTP nick end labeling (TUNEL) staining. Apoptotic cells in the intestinal sections were identified according to the TUNEL staining method using a commercial kit (Roche Diagnostics Corp., Indianapolis, IN, USA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. The apoptotic index was defined as the percentage of TUNEL-positive cells (red stain) in 100 randomly chosen intraepithelial cells as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
